ROCm WMMA-based prefill matmul

Status: PROPOSED (codex recommendation 2026-05-09, long-term)

Goal:
Use RDNA3.5 wave32 WMMA builtins to feed matrix-tile hardware on the
dense Q8_0 prefill path.  Closest gfx1151 analogue to Metal
simdgroup_matmul; needed to plausibly close the 8.4x prefill gap
(29.7 -> 250 t/s).

Why:
Metal hits ~250 t/s prefill via simdgroup_matmul tiling.  Current ROCm
uses scalar wave-per-row kernels that do not feed WMMA-shaped work.
AMDGCN exposes:
  __builtin_amdgcn_wmma_i32_16x16x16_iu8_w32 (a_sign, a4, b_sign, b4, c8, clamp)
  __builtin_amdgcn_wmma_f16_16x16x16_f16_w32 (a16, b16, c16, opsel)

For DSv4 quant mix:
- Q8_0 dense prefill: WMMA_I8 with activation int8 microquant
- F16 dense paths: WMMA_F16 directly
- IQ2/Q2 routed: NOT directly WMMA-able without weight transformation

File pointers:
- Q8_0 wave + tile matmul: /home/noah/repos/ds4/ds4_rocm.c:566+, 633+
- F16 matmul: search rocm_matmul_f16_*
- Decode Q8_0 already at 185 GiB/s ceiling so won't help decode

Next steps:
1. Decide on activation microquant (see tsk for sdot4 -- shared
   prerequisite; if accepted, use same microquant + scales here)
2. Prototype WMMA_I8 kernel for Q8_0 matmul at out_dim x n_tok shape with
   16x16 tiles
3. Tile alignment: pad in_dim/out_dim/n_tok to multiples of 16
4. Compare to current tile kernel at end-to-end
5. Microbench in tests/ds4_rocm_matmul_bench.c (extend with --wmma flag)

Complexity: ~1000-2000 lines, 3-5 days.  Tile alignment + correctness
are the hard parts.

Related:
- depends on activation microquant from sdot4 task
- tsk-22 FlashAttention (could also use WMMA inside FA)
- tsk-10 rocBLAS/hipBLASLt evaluation (alternative)

Note: clpeak says theoretical f16 GEMM peak on this hardware ~30 TFLOPS
and Q8_0 decode is bandwidth-bound at 25 t/s ceiling.  Prefill compute-
bound regime may be where Metal pulls ahead, but 250 t/s requires either
WMMA or much higher token reuse than current kernels expose.